|f}}, {{t+|hi|दशा|f}}, {{t+|hi|स्थिति|f}}\n* Hungarian: {{tt+|hu|állapot}}\n* Icelandic: {{tt|is|ástand|n}}\n* Ido: {{tt+|io|stando}}\n* Indonesian: {{tt+|id|keadaan}}\n* Irish: {{tt|ga|stát|m}}\n* Italian: {{tt+|it|stato|m}}\n* Japanese: {{tt+|ja|状態|tr=じょうたい, jōtai}}\n* Kazakh: {{tt|kk|жағдай}}\n* Korean: {{tt+|ko|상태(狀態)}}\n* Kyrgyz: {{tt+|ky|абал}}\n* Ladin: {{tt|lld|stat|m}}\n* Latgalian: {{tt|ltg|stāte|f}}\n* Latin: {{tt+|la|status|m}}\n* Latvian: {{tt|lv|stāvoklis|m}}\n* Lithuanian: {{tt+|lt|būsena|f}}, {{tt+|lt|būklė|f}}\n* Macedonian: {{tt|mk|состојба|f}}\n* Malay: {{tt+|ms|keadaan}}\n* Māori: {{t|mi|hanga}} {{qualifier|referring to matter}}\n* Mongolian:\n*: Cyrillic: {{tt+|mn|байдал}}\n* Norman: {{t|nrf|êtat|m}}\n* Norwegian:\n*: Bokmål: {{t+|nb|tilstand|m}}\n* Old English: {{t|ang|steall|m}}\n* Pashto: {{tt+|ps|حالت|m|tr=hālat}}\n* Persian:\n*: Classical Persian: {{t|fa-cls|حَالَت}}, {{t|fa-cls|حَال}}\n*: Iranian Persian: {{tt|fa-ira|حالَت}}, {{t+|fa-ira|حال}}\n* Polish: {{tt+|pl|stan|m}}, {{tt+|pl|kondycja|f}}\n* Portuguese: {{tt+|pt|estado|m}}\n* Romanian: {{tt+|ro|stare|f}}, {{tt+|ro|stat|n}}\n* Russian: {{tt+|ru|состоя́ние|n}}, {{tt+|ru|положе́ние|n}}, {{tt+|ru|ста́тус|m}}\n* Sanskrit: {{tt+|sa|अवस्था|f}}\n* Sardinian: {{t|sc|istadu|m}}, {{t|sc|istatu|m}}, {{t|sc|stadu|m}}\n* Scottish Gaelic: {{tt|gd|cor|m}}\n* Serbo-Croatian:\n*: Cyrillic: {{tt|sh|ста́ње|n}}, {{tt+|sh|pȍložāj|m}}\n*: Latin: {{tt+|sh|stánje|n}}, {{tt+|sh|pȍložāj|m}}\n* Sicilian: {{tt|scn|statu|m}}\n* Slovak: {{tt|sk|stav|m}}\n* Slovene: {{tt+|sl|stanje|n}}\n* Spanish: {{tt+|es|estado|m}}\n* Swahili: {{tt+|sw|hali}}\n* Swedish: {{tt+|sv|tillstånd|n}}\n* Tagalog: {{tt|tl|himtang}}\n* Tajik: {{tt|tg|ҳолат}}, {{t|tg|ҳол}}\n* Tarifit: {{t|rif|rḥar|m}}\n* Thai: {{tt+|th|สภาพ}}, {{tt+|th|ภาวะ}}, {{t+|th|สภาวะ|tr=sà-paa-wá}}\n* Turkish: {{tt+|tr|durum}}, {{tt+|tr|hâl}}\n*: Ottoman Turkish: {{t|ota|بال|tr=bâl}}, {{t|ota|پره‌سه|tr=perese}}\n* Turkmen: {{tt|tk|ýagdaýy}}\n* Ukrainian: {{tt+|uk|стан|m}}, {{tt|uk|стано́вище|n}}\n* Urdu: {{tt|ur|حالَت|f}}, {{tt+|ur|حال|m}}\n* Uzbek: {{tt+|uz|ahvol}}, {{tt+|uz|holat}}\n* Venetan: {{tt|vec|stato|m}}, {{tt|vec|stado|m}}\n* Vietnamese: {{tt+|vi|tình trạng}}, {{tt+|vi|trạng thái}}, {{tt+|vi|chế độ}}\n* Walloon: {{tt+|wa|estance|f}}\n* Yiddish: {{t|yi|צושטאַנד|m}}\n* Zazaki: {{tt+|zza|hal|c}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top|computing: the stable condition of a processor during a particular clock cycle}}\n* Arabic: {{t+|ar|وَضْع|m}}\n* Aramaic:\n*: Assyrian Neo-Aramaic: {{t|aii|ܩܝܵܡܵܐ|m}}\n* Bulgarian: {{tt+|bg|състоя́ние|n}}\n* Catalan: {{tt+|ca|estat|m}}\n* Czech: {{tt+|cs|stav|m}}\n* Finnish: {{tt+|fi|tila}}\n* German: {{tt+|de|Zustand|m}}\n* Greek: {{tt+|el|κατάσταση|f}}\n* Japanese: {{tt+|ja|状態|tr=じょうたい, jōtai}}\n* Korean: {{tt+|ko|상태(狀態)}}\n* Polish: {{tt+|pl|stan|m}}\n* Portuguese: {{tt+|pt|estado|m}}\n* Romanian: {{tt+|ro|stare|f}}\n* Russian: {{tt+|ru|состоя́ние|n}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top|computing: the set of all parameters relevant to a computation}}\n* Catalan: {{tt+|ca|estat|m}}\n* Czech: {{tt+|cs|stav|m}}\n* Finnish: {{tt+|fi|tila}}\n* Hungarian: {{tt+|hu|állapot}}\n* Italian: {{tt+|it|stato|m}}\n* Japanese: {{tt+|ja|状態|tr=じょうたい, jōtai}}, {{tt+|ja|ステート|tr=sutēto}}\n* Polish: {{tt+|pl|stan|m}}\n* Portuguese: {{tt+|pt|estado|m}}\n* Romanian: {{tt+|ro|stare|f}}\n* Russian: {{tt+|ru|состоя́ние|n}}\n* Spanish: {{tt+|es|estado|m}}\n* Swahili: {{tt+|sw|hali}}\n* Vietnamese: {{tt+|vi|trạng thái}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top|computing: the values of all parameters at some point in a computation}}\n* Catalan: {{tt+|ca|estat|m}}\n* Czech: {{tt+|cs|stav|m}}\n* Finnish: {{tt+|fi|tila}}\n* Hungarian: {{tt+|hu|állapot}}\n* Italian: {{tt+|it|stato|m}}\n* Japanese: {{tt+|ja|状態|tr=じょうたい, jōtai}}, {{tt+|ja|ステート|tr=sutēto}}\n* Polish: {{tt+|pl|stan|m}}\n* Portuguese: {{tt+|pt|estado|m}}\n* Romanian: {{tt+|ro|stare|f}}\n* Russian: {{tt+|ru|состоя́ние|n}}\n* Spanish: {{tt+|es|estado|m}}\n* Swahili: {{tt+|sw|hali}}\n* Vietnamese: {{tt+|vi|trạng thái}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top|math: an element of the range of random variables}}\n* German: {{tt+|de|Zustand|m}}\n* Hebrew: {{tt+|he|מַצָּב|m|tr=matsáv}}\n* Japanese: {{tt+|ja|状態|tr=じょうたい, jōtai}}\n* Latin: {{tt+|la|elementum|n}}\n* Vietnamese: {{tt+|vi|trạng thái}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{checktrans-top}}\n* Interlingua: {{t-check|ia|stato}}\n* Swedish: {{t+check|sv|nation|c}}, {{t+check|sv|land|n}}\n}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n===Verb===\n{{en-verb}}\n\n# {{lb|en|transitive}} To [[declare]] to be a [[fact]].\n#: {{ux|en|He '''stated''' that he was willing to help.}}\n#* {{RQ:Hough Purchase Price|chapter=II|text=Carried somehow, somewhither, for some reason, on these surging floods, were these travelers, of errand not wholly obvious to their fellows, yet of such sort as to call into query alike the nature of their errand and their own relations. It is easily earned repetition to '''state''' that Josephine St. Auban's was a presence not to be concealed.}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=1994|author=Congress of the United States|title=[[s: Page:United_States_Statutes_at_Large_Volume_108_Part_4.djvu/746|United States Statutes at Large]]|volume=108|others=part 4|passage=A provision of law may not be construed as requiring a new grant to be awarded to a specified non-Federal Government entity unless that provision of law (1) specifically refers to this subsection; specifically identifies the particular non-Federal Government entity involved; and (3) specifically '''states''' that the award to that entity is required by such provision of law in contravention of the policy set forth in subsection (a).}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=1996|translator=w:Robert D. Martin|title=The Natural Science of the Human Species|author=w:Konrad Lorenz|location=Cambridge, MA|publisher=MIT Press|chapter=5|page=93|url=https://archive.org/details/naturalscienceof0000lore\n|passage=The ''species-preserving'' purposivity of higher organisms is no greater than that of the lowest forms of life, and Jakob von Uexküll was entirely justified in '''stating''' that all living organisms are ''equally well'' adapted to their environments.}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=2017|author=K R Wadhwaney|title=Indian Cricket Controversies|passage=When Tony Greig, in a meaningful and provocative interview, asked Sarfaraz background of betting and match-fixing, the Pakistan \"superbat\" categorically '''stated''' that it should start with Asif Iqbal and Gavaskar who, according to him, were the \"original fixers\"..}}\n# {{lb|en|transitive}} To make [[known]].\n#: {{ux|en|'''State''' your intentions.}}\n\n====Usage notes====\n''State'' is stronger or more definitive than ''say''. It is used to communicate an absence of reasonable doubt and to emphasize the factual or truthful nature of the communication.  The poet and journalist William Cullen Bryant listed ''state'', when used as a synonym for ''say'', in his style guide for ''The New York Evening Post'', which he called the \"Index Expurgatorius\".\n\nSome journalists prefer to follow the formula that \"People ''say'' things, and documents ''state'' things\".\n\n====Synonyms====\n* See [[Thesaurus:communicate]]\n\n====Derived terms====\n{{col|en|state the obvious|counterstate|forestate|misstate|overstate|restate|statable|statement|stater|understate|unstate}}\n\n====Translations====\n{{trans-top-also|declare to be a fact|assert|declare|affirm}}{{multitrans|data=\n* Aramaic:\n*: Assyrian Neo-Aramaic: {{t|aii|ܒܲܕܸܩ}}, {{t|aii|ܒܲܝܸܢ}}\n* Bulgarian: {{tt+|bg|заявявам}}, {{tt+|bg|изразявам}}\n* Catalan: {{tt+|ca|declarar}}\n* Chinese:\n*: Mandarin: {{tt+|cmn|表示|tr=biǎoshì}}, {{tt+|cmn|聲明|tr=shēngmíng}}, {{tt+|cmn|規定|tr=guīdìng}}\n* Danish: {{tt|da|erklære}}\n* Dutch: {{tt+|nl|verklaren}}\n* Finnish: {{tt+|fi|sanoa}}, {{tt+|fi|todeta}}, {{tt+|fi|ilmoittaa}}\n* French: {{tt+|fr|déclarer}}\n* German: {{tt+|de|erklären}}\n* Greek: {{tt+|el|δηλώνω}}\n* Hebrew: {{tt|he|הצהיר|tr=hits'hír}}\n* Hungarian: {{tt+|hu|kijelent}}, {{tt+|hu|megállapít}}\n* Italian: {{tt+|it|dichiarare}}, {{tt+|it|statuire}}\n* Japanese: {{tt+|ja|述べる|tr=noberu}}\n* Korean: {{tt+|ko|표현}}\n* Latin: {{tt+|la|eloquor}}, {{tt+|la|dico}}\n* Māori: {{tt|mi|tauākī}}, {{tt|mi|whakapuaki}}\n* Polish: {{tt+|pl|twierdzić|impf}}, {{tt+|pl|stwierdzać|impf}}, {{tt+|pl|stwierdzić|pf}}\n* Portuguese: {{tt+|pt|atestar}}\n* Romanian: {{tt+|ro|declara}}\n* Russian: {{tt+|ru|утвержда́ть|impf}}, {{tt+|ru|утверди́ть|pf}}, {{tt+|ru|заявля́ть|impf}}, {{tt+|ru|заяви́ть|pf}}, {{tt+|ru|констати́ровать|impf|pf}}\n* Serbo-Croatian: {{tt+|sh|izjaviti}}, {{tt+|sh|izneti}}\n* Spanish: {{t+|es|aseverar}}\n* Swahili: {{tt+|sw|hali}}\n* Swedish: {{tt+|sv|påstå}}\n* Tagalog: {{tt+|tl|estado}}\n* Thai: {{t+|th|กล่าว|tr=glàao}}, {{t+|th|แถลง|tr=tà-lɛ̌ɛng}}\n* Turkish: {{t+|tr|bildirmek}}\n* Ukrainian: {{t|uk|заявля́ти|impf}}, {{t|uk|заяви́ти|pf}}, {{t|uk|стве́рджувати|impf}}, {{t|uk|стве́рдити|pf}}, {{t|uk|констатува́ти|impf|pf}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top-see|make known|declare|indicate|enunciate}}\n* Arabic: {{tt|ar|يُبْدِي|m}}\n* Bulgarian: {{tt+|bg|обявявам}}, {{tt+|bg|съобщавам}}\n* Catalan: {{tt+|ca|declarar}}\n* Chinese:\n*: Mandarin: {{tt+|cmn|表示|tr=biǎoshì}}, {{tt+|cmn|陳述|tr=chénshù}}, {{tt+|cmn|聲明|tr=shēngmíng}}\n* Dutch: {{tt+|nl|bekendmaken}}\n* Finnish: {{tt+|fi|ilmoittaa}}\n* French: {{tt+|fr|indiquer}}\n* German: {{tt+|de|darlegen}}, {{tt+|de|nennen}}\n* Greek: {{tt+|el|διατυπώνω}}, {{tt+|el|εκθέτω}}\n* Hindi: {{t+|hi|उल्लेख|m}}\n* Hungarian: {{tt+|hu|közöl}}\n* Irish: {{tt|ga|sonraigh}}, {{t|ga|cuir in iúl}}\n* Italian: {{tt+|it|dichiarare}}, {{tt+|it|esporre}}, {{tt+|it|indicare}}\n* Japanese: {{tt+|ja|述べる|tr=noberu}}\n* Kapampangan: {{t|pam|ipasiag}} {{qualifier|traditional}}, {{t|pam|ipasyag}} {{qualifier|modern}}\n* Korean: {{tt+|ko|선언}}\n* Latin: {{tt+|la|eloquor}}, {{tt+|la|dico}}\n* Māori: {{tt|mi|whakapuaki}}, {{tt|mi|taukī}}\n* Polish: {{tt+|pl|oznajmiać|impf}}, {{tt+|pl|oznajmić|pf}}\n* Portuguese: {{tt+|pt|declarar}}, {{tt+|pt|indicar}}\n* Russian: {{tt+|ru|объявля́ть|impf}}, {{tt+|ru|объяви́ть|pf}}, {{tt+|ru|излага́ть|impf}}, {{tt+|ru|изложи́ть|pf}}\n* Swahili: {{tt+|sw|hali}}\n* Swedish: {{tt+|sv|ange}}\n* Tagalog: {{t|tl|ipahayag}}\n* Thai: {{t+|th|แจ้ง|tr=jɛ̂ɛng}}\n* Turkish: {{t+|tr|belirtmek}}, {{t+|tr|bildirmek}}\n}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{checktrans-top}}\n* Arabic: {{t-check|ar|قَرَرَ}}\n* Korean: {{t+check|ko|말하다}}\n* Swedish: {{t+check|sv|förklara}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n===Adjective===\n{{en-adj}}\n\n# {{lb|en|obsolete}} [[stately|Stately]].\n#* {{RQ:Spenser Shepheardes Calender|chapter=September|folio=36|passage=The ſhepheardes ſwayne you cannot well ken, / But it be by his pride, from other men: / They looken bigge as Bulles, that bene bate, / And bearen the cragge ſo ſtiffe and ſo '''ſtate,''' / As Cocke on his dunghill, crowing cranck.|year=1586}}\n\n===Related terms===\n* {{l|en|estate}}\n* {{l|en|statistics}}\n* {{l|en|status}}\n* {{l|en|State}}\n\n===See also===\n* {{l|en|department}}\n* {{l|en|province}}\n\n===References===\n* {{R:OneLook}}\n* {{R:Keywords 21st}}\n* {{R:Webster 1913}}\n* {{R:Century 1911}}\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{pedia}}\n\n===Anagrams===\n* {{anagrams|en|a=aestt|Tates|Teats|teats|Tetas|taste|atest|Testa|testa|aetts|Satet}}\n\n{{cln|en|raising verbs|reporting verbs}}\n{{C|en|Administrative divisions|Collectives|Talking}}\n\n==Afrikaans==\n\n===Noun===\n{{head|af|noun form}}\n\n# {{plural of|af|staat}}\n\n==Italian==\n\n===Pronunciation===\n{{it-pr|stàte}}\n\n===Etymology 1===\n[[apheresis|Apheretic]] form of {{m|it|estate}}.\n\n====Noun====\n{{it-noun|f}}\n\n# {{tlb|it|Tuscan}} {{alt form|it|estate}}\n#* {{quote-book|it|year=1567|title=Ricettario fiorentino|trans-title=Florentine Cookbook|url=https://books.google.it/books?id=YX5DAAAAcAAJ&printsec=frontcover&dq=Ricettario+fiorentino&hl=it&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwia8e3b85zhAhWKM-wKHaURCa4Q6AEIKTAA#v=onepage&q&f=false|page=5|pageurl=https://books.google.it/books?id=YX5DAAAAcAAJ&dq=Ricettario%20fiorentino&hl=it&pg=PA5#v=onepage&q&f=false|passage=L'ACQVA buona {{...}} debbe toﬅo riſcaldarſi, e raffreddarſi, e la ''' ﬅate''' eſſere freſca, e l'inuerno tiepida.|translation=Good water should quickly heat up, and cool down; and be cool during Summer, and lukewarm during Winter.}}\n\n===Etymology 2===\n{{nonlemma}}\n\n====Verb====\n{{head|it|verb form}}\n\n# {{inflection of|it|stare||2|p|pres|ind|;|2|p|imp}}\n\n===Etymology 3===\n{{nonlemma}}\n\n====Participle====\n{{head|it|past participle form|g=f-p}}\n\n# {{feminine plural of|it|stato}}\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{R:it:Olivetti}}\n\n===Anagrams===\n* {{anagrams|it|a=aestt|Setta|setta|testa}}\n\n==Latin==\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{la-IPA|stāte|ann=1}}\n* {{la-IPA|state|ann=1}}\n\n===Verb===\n{{head|la|verb form|head=stāte}}\n\n# {{inflection of|la|stō||2|p|pres|actv|impr}}\n\n===Participle===\n{{head|la|participle form}}\n\n# {{inflection of|la|status||voc|m|s}}\n\n==Romanian==\n\n===Noun===\n{{head|ro|noun form}}\n\n# {{plural of|ro|stat}}\n\n==Yola==\n\n===Etymology===\nFrom {{inh|yol|enm|stat}}, from {{der|yol|fro|estat}}, from {{der|yol|la|status}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|yol|/staːt/}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{head|yol|noun}}\n\n# [[condition]]\n#* {{quote-book|yol|year=1867|line=1-2|page=116|title=CONGRATULATORY ADDRESS IN THE DIALECT OF FORTH AND BARGY|passage=Ye '''state''' na dicke daie o'ye londe, na whilke be nar fash nar moile, albiet 'constitutional agitation,'|translation=The '''condition''', this day, of the country, in which is neither tumult nor disorder, but that constitutional agitation,}}\n\n===References===\n* {{R:Poole 1867|page=116}}"}}